  - Use Tailwind CSS 4 for styling components
  - Use UI components from ~/components/ui (Button, Input, Text, etc.)
  - Use next-intl for internationalization
  - SEO optimization:
    * Use appropriate meta tags (title, description)
    * Implement structured data (JSON-LD)
    * Use semantic HTML elements
    * Ensure proper heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3, etc.)
    * Use Next.js metadata API to configure page metadata
    * Add alt text to all images
  - Follow the project directory structure:
    * src/app/ - Next.js App Router pages and navigation
    * src/app/[locale]/ - Internationalized routes using next-intl
    * src/components/ - Shared components
    * src/lib/ - Utility libraries and functions
    * src/config/ - Configuration files
    * src/locales/ - Internationalization JSON files
    * src/styles/ - Global stylesheets
    * public/ - Static assets
  - For new packages, use 'pnpm install <package-name>'
  - Write unit tests for utilities and complex components (.test.tsx)
  </next_js_coding>

